cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with substructural logics and their properties. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of logic in AI and the implications of different logical systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of logic in programming and the translation of classical logic into intuitionistic logic. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of proofs in intuitionistic affine logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of derived connectives and their applications.
